               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Zubdat al-maqāmāt</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010113603 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85089787" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1034-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Rare hagiography of the 
                <orgName>Naqshbandī</orgName>Ṣūfī saint 
                <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100167544703.0x000001 viaf_314814912" role="subject">Khvājah Muḥammad al-Bāqī [ibn ʿAbd al-Salām] al-Uvaysī al-Naqshbandī</persName>(d. 1012/1603), better known as 
                <persName key="viaf_314814912" role="subject">Shaykh ʿAbd al-Bāqī</persName>, who was also the spiritual preceptor of the 
                <orgName>Mujaddidī Naqshbandī</orgName>saint, 
                <persName key="viaf_32839461" role="oth">Shaykh Aḥmad Fārūqī</persName>(d. 1034/1624), written by an unnamed author (from Central Asia) who is an ardent follower of 
                <persName key="person_f8093" role="oth">Shaykh Burhān al-Dīn "Gharīb"</persName>and supplies valuable information on contemporary seventeenth-century social life and religious networks.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work was written at the request of 
                <persName key="person_f8094" role="pat">Amīr Muḥammad Nuʿmān</persName>, the khalīfah or successor of the sheikh at 
                <placeName>Burhānpūr</placeName>(
                <placeName>Deccan</placeName>), begun 1031/1622 and completed after nearly two years in the vicinity of 
                <placeName>Lāhawr</placeName>under the guidance of 
                <placeName>Mawlānā ʿAbd al-Muʾmin Lāhawrī</placeName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is comprised of two sections termed maqṣad with further subdivisions into faṣl, etcetera.</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon, damaged (f. 314v): completed by 5 Shaʿbān 11[0]5/1 April 1694.</p>
                        <p>Related and unrelated detached notes and fragments bound following the colophon.</p>
                        <p>Neat nastaʿlīq-i khafī.</p>
                        <p>Rebound in a IOL red leather binding, date stamped 15[05]1981.</p>
                        <p>Folios and fragments entirely remounted in new margins, with fine gauze overlay throughout. Substantial losses from margins, catchwords, and annotations; wormholes; stains.</p>
                        <p>IOL microfilm 3141.</p>
                     </note>
